TITLE: User Information Command Implementation for Discord.js
DESCRIPTION: A slash command that provides information about the user who triggered the command, including their username and when they joined the server, demonstrating interaction with user and member objects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordjs/guide/blob/main/guide/creating-your-bot/slash-commands.md#2025-04-09_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { SlashCommandBuilder } = require('discord.js');

module.exports = {
	data: new SlashCommandBuilder()
		.setName('user')
		.setDescription('Provides information about the user.'),
	async execute(interaction) {
		// interaction.user is the object representing the User who ran the command
		// interaction.member is the GuildMember object, which represents the user in the specific guild
		await interaction.reply(`This command was run by ${interaction.user.username}, who joined on ${interaction.member.joinedAt}.`);
	},
};
```

