TITLE: Executing a Slash Command and Parsing Options in Discord.js
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to retrieve and use the values of command options in the execute method. It shows accessing the 'target' user and 'reason' string, with a default value for the optional reason.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordjs/guide/blob/main/guide/slash-commands/parsing-options.md#2025-04-09_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
	// data: new SlashCommandBuilder()...
	async execute(interaction) {
		const target = interaction.options.getUser('target');
		const reason = interaction.options.getString('reason') ?? 'No reason provided';

		await interaction.reply(`Banning ${target.username} for reason: ${reason}`);
		await interaction.guild.members.ban(target);
	},
};
```

